hopobject.body: I work for a publishers colorado laboratory psc st. francis medical center colorado springs co To a certain extent, the CDC has been flying blind when it comes to food-borne illnesses for the past week because the government shutdown meant it had to close PulseNet. That's a national computer network that connects 87 public health laboratories and look for trends and matches to spot food-borne illness outbreaks. It's one of the agency's most important tools in detecting this kind of problem.
